# SPACED - Homepage CTA Plan (Call To Action)


— WEDGE ANCHOR —

Need a private place right now? Book a room near you in minutes.

Core moment:
Immediate need for discreet, short-duration private space.

————————————
Goal

Make the homepage communicate MVP value in under 5 seconds and drive users to one action: explore and book now.

Primary user emotion to trigger

- "I can get a private space near me right now, with no friction."

Core value proposition (hero-level)

- Private space on demand.
- Nearby, discreet, and ready in minutes.
- Start with 30-60 minutes, extend anytime.

---

Homepage message hierarchy

1) First screen (hero) = promise + proof + CTA
- [ ] Headline focused on immediate outcome.
- [ ] Subheadline with speed + discretion + flexibility.
- [ ] Primary CTA: Explore spaces now.
- [ ] Secondary CTA: How it works (or Book in 60s).
- [ ] Quick trust chips under CTA:
  - [ ] "Available now"
  - [ ] "No commitment"
  - [ ] "Instant access"

2) How it works (3 steps)
- [ ] Discover nearby spaces.
- [ ] Choose 30 or 60 minutes.
- [ ] Book, pay, and receive access instructions.
- [ ] Micro-CTA after steps: "See available spaces."

3) Use-case cards (emotion-driven)
- [ ] Private encounter
- [ ] Short reset / rest
- [ ] Temporary privacy
- [ ] Each card includes one specific benefit and one short CTA.

4) Social proof / trust section
- [ ] Rating + review count snapshot.
- [ ] "Access-ready spaces" metric (even if mocked in MVP).
- [ ] Discretion and reliability statement.

5) Final conversion block
- [ ] Clear urgency copy ("ready in minutes").
- [ ] Repeated primary CTA.
- [ ] Optional secondary CTA for hesitant users.

---

Copy checklist (must pass)

- [ ] Benefit-first wording (not feature-first).
- [ ] No mixed language in one screen.
- [ ] Keep headlines short and concrete.
- [ ] Every section has one intended action.
- [ ] Remove decorative text that does not improve conversion.

---

CTA variants to test (MVP)

- [ ] Variant A button: "Explore spaces"
- [ ] Variant B button: "Book now"
- [ ] Variant C button: "Find a private space near me"

Success metrics (front-end measurable now)

- [ ] Hero CTA click-through rate.
- [ ] Home -> spaces page click rate.
- [ ] Home -> booking flow start rate.
- [ ] Scroll depth to final CTA.

---

Implementation order

Phase 1 (high impact, low complexity)
- [ ] Rewrite hero copy + CTA labels.
- [ ] Add trust chips under hero CTA.
- [ ] Add "How it works" 3-step strip.
- [ ] Add final repeated CTA block.

Phase 2 (conversion quality)
- [ ] Tighten use-case card copy.
- [ ] Add social proof module.
- [ ] Add simple event tracking hooks for CTA clicks.

Phase 3 (optimization)
- [ ] Run CTA copy A/B test.
- [ ] Tune section order and visual density from real click data.

---

Guardrails

- [ ] Keep homepage focused on one primary action.
- [ ] Avoid too many equal-weight CTAs above the fold.
- [ ] Do not ship major style-only changes without conversion intent.
